Talent Acquisition Internship MEA United Arab Emirates-Dubai-Dubai
03 May 2014 12:29 AM - UAE
!*!Position Summary:As Talent Acquisition Intern in the MEA HR team you will assist in all administrative and operational tasks involved within many stages of the recruitment process.  This is an ideal opportunity for someone looking for a third year university placement who is interested in pursuing a career in recruitment and HR. What will it be like to work for Hilton Worldwide? With thousands of hotels in more than 80 countries, Hilton Worldwide offers countless opportunities to delight. From an open door to a welcoming smile and an exceptional experience, we offer the millions of travelers who stay with us every year a welcome they will never forget.If you understand the importance of a proper welcome and know how to offer an exceptional hospitality experience, you may be just the person we are looking for to work as a Team Member with Hilton Worldwide. Because itâs with Hilton Worldwide where we never forget the reason we're here: to delight our guests, Team Members, and owners alike.  What will I be doing? Recruitment Support 75%Assists in producing internal & external recruitment adverts Responds to candidate enquiries regarding working at Hilton Worldwide or carrying out work experienceResponds to candidates who send in their CVs speculativelyAttends recruitment fairs as requiredAssists in maintaining user access to the Taleo applicant tracking system Acts as day to day contact for all hotel queries relating to the system and its usageAssists with the creation of adverts on LinkedInFormatting of online job descriptionsMaintains records of all recruitment related expenditure incurredAssists in setting up the room in preparation for online psychometric testing of candidatesAssists with meeting candidates for interview/assessmentsAssists in the organisation of interviews/assessmentsAssists with recruitment projects as requiredAssists with the use of social media in our recruitment ie Facebook, Twitter and LinkedInYou will also take on a study related project as part of the placement. Administrative support 25%Manages a variety of departmental administration including but not limited to photocopying, assisting with emails, invoicing and cross chargingProduces reports and management information within the required timescalesAssists with weekly new hires reports where necessaryOccasionally make travel arrangements What are we looking for? The individual should possess the following knowledge, skills and abilities and be able to perform the essential functions of the job, with or without reasonable accommodation.Excellent written and verbal communication skills including the ability to explain complex analytical topics to a wide audience.Flexible approach and excellent time management skillsAbsolute discretion with confidential informationAbility to work under pressure and effectively handle multiple, concurrent demands Excellent administrative skillsFluency in English languageGood people skillsPlanning and organising skillsGood analytical skillsExcellent attention to detailGood knowledge of social mediaWhat benefits will I receive?Your benefits will include a competitive starting salary and holiday entitlement. As an employee you will become a member of the The Hilton Club which provides reduced hotel room rates in our hotels worldwide, plus discounts on products and services offered by Hi (more...)
